    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1474"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1474">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2178.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 71.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 71, of
                    August 23, 1912, transmitting correspondence regarding the peace proposals of
                    General Mena, the violation by the rebels of the armistice arranged by the
                    Salvadoran Minister, and the protests of the Diplomatic Corps and the Consular
                    officers in Managua against the bombardment of the city by Generals Mena and
                    Zeledón.</p>
                <p>Your action in endeavoring to assist in reaching a peaceful solution of the
                    conflict between the Government and General Mena, and in taking the wise
                    measures adopted by you for the defense of American and other interests after
                    hostilities were resumed, is approved by the Department.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
